The paper proposes a method for policy evaluation using the LSTD algorithm with a focus on reducing complexity, making it suitable for big data settings. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper applies the method to a traffic signal control problem, indicating a potential connection to the systems and control (cs.SY) or robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper provides convergence rate results and finite-time bounds, suggesting a possible connection to the mathematics (math) sub-category.
